 uniform random variables, but for $t \\leq t_{\\mathrm{crit}}$ the\nGibbs conditioning principle comes into play, and here there is a parameter\n$\\beta_t>0$ (the inverse temperature) such that the coordinates are\napproximately distributed according to a density proportional to $e^{\n-\\beta_t\\phi(s)}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Dec 2020 18:46:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-22"}
