ral networks. The method\ncan effectively and robustly reconstruct high-quality images from highly\nundersampled dynamic multi-coil data ($16 \\times$ and $24 \\times$ yielding 15s\nand 10s scan times respectively) with fast reconstruction speed (2.8s). This\ncould potentially facilitate achieving fast single-breath-hold clinical 2D\ncardiac cine imaging.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Dec 2020 12:52:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 18 Jun 2021 13:20:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-21"}
